The paper focuses on facial landmark detection and analysis, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Canonical Correlation Analysis (CCA), which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also mentions the use of benchmarks and annotations, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the facial landmark correlation analysis, which could be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) research.
